record_data.record_plain_text: EXHIBIT 9.16 INSURANCE REQUIREMENTS Commencing as indicated herein below and at all times thereafter during the term of this Agreement (unless otherwise expressly indicated below), Rush Springs Storage shall procure and maintain the following minimum insurance, with insurers rated “A-” VII or higher by A.M. Best’s Key Rating Guide that are licensed to do business in the State of Oklahoma: Prior to commencing construction on the Rush Springs Storage Project, Workers’ Compensation Insurance for statutory obligations imposed by Applicable Laws, including, where applicable, the Alternate Employer Endorsement, the United States Longshoremen’s and Harbor Workers’ Act, the Maritime Coverage and the Jones Act. Prior to commencing construction on the Rush Springs Storage Project, Employers’ Liability Insurance, including Occupational Disease, shall be provided with a limit of (i) One Million Dollars ($1,000,000) for bodily injury per accident, (ii) One Million Dollars ($1,000,000) for bodily injury by disease per policy, and (iii) One Million Dollars ($1,000,000) for bodily injury by disease per employee. Prior to commencing construction on the Rush Springs Storage Project, Business Automobile Liability Insurance which shall apply to all owned, non-owned, leased, and hired automobiles with a limit of One Million Dollars ($1,000,000) per accident for bodily injury and property damage. Prior to commencing construction on the Rush Springs Storage Project, Commercial General Liability Insurance which shall apply to liability arising out of premises, operations, bodily injury, property damage, products and completed operations and liability insured under and assumed contract (contractual liability), with a limit of One Million Dollars ($1,000,000) per occurrence, Two Million Dollars ($2,000,000) aggregate. The products and completed operations coverage insurance shall be provided for the duration of any applicable warranty period. Prior to commencing construction on the Rush Springs Storage Project, Umbrella or Excess Liability Insurance which shall apply to Employers Liability, Commercial General Liability and Business Automobile Liability Insurance, required in (b), (c), and (d) above, with a limit of Thirty Million Dollars ($30,000,000) per occurrence and Thirty Million Dollars ($30,000,000) aggregate. Prior to commencing construction on the Rush Springs Storage Project and until the date the Rush Springs Storage Project commences commercial operations, All Risk Installation and Builder’s Risk Insurance or All Risk or Special Perils Property Insurance including Equipment Breakdown with limits of insurance written on a replacement cost basis, including sublimits for wind, earthquake, and flood exposures. Prior to commencing construction on the Rush Springs Storage Project, Pollution Liability Insurance, including on-site clean up coverage, applicable to damages that Rush Springs Wind becomes legally obligated to pay for bodily injury; property damage, including loss of use of damaged property or of property that has not been physically injured or destroyed; cleanup costs; and defense, including costs and expenses incurred in the investigation, defense, or settlement of claims; all in connection with a pollution incident which has migrated from the insured facility. Coverage shall apply to sudden and accidental pollution conditions resulting from the escape or release of smoke, vapors, fumes, acids, alkalis, toxic chemicals, liquids, or gases, waste materials, or other irritants, contaminants, or pollutants. Coverage shall be maintained in an amount of at least $1,000,000 per incident. On the date Rush Springs Project commences commercial operations , All-Risk Property insurance which shall include: (i) coverage for fire, flood, wind storm, tornado and earthquake with respect to facilities similar in construction, location and occupancy to the Facility, with sublimits of no less than $10,000,000 each for flood and earthquake; (ii) Boiler and Machinery insurance covering all objects customarily subject to such insurance, on a replacement cost basis; and (iii) Business Interruption insurance coverage in an amount required to cover continuing expenses resulting from interruption for a period of twelve (12) calendar months and loss of revenues by reason of total or partial suspension or delay of, or interruption in, operations.

Execution Version SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT THIS SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT (this “Agreement”), is entered into as of ____________, 2019 (the “Effective Date”), by and between Rush Springs Wind Energy, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (together with its successors and permitted assigns, “Rush Springs Wind”) and Rush Springs Energy Storage, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (together with its successors and permitted assigns, “Rush Springs Storage,” and together with Rush Springs Wind, the “Parties” and each a “Party”). RECITALS WHEREAS, Rush Springs Wind owns and operates a wind energy generation facility with a nameplate capacity of approximately 250 MW (net) (the “Rush Springs Wind Project”); WHEREAS, Rush Springs Storage is developing and will own and operate a battery energy storage facility with a nameplate capacity of approximately 10.3 MW (the “Rush Springs Storage Project”, (under an interconnection agreement that allows for a project of 20 MW), together with the Rush Springs Wind Project, the “Projects” and each a “Project”); WHEREAS, Rush Springs Wind entered into a certain Generator Interconnection Agreement, by and among itself, Southwest Power Pool (“SPP”) and AEP Oklahoma Transmission Company, Inc. (“AEP”), originally dated as of October 23, 2015 (the “Rush Springs Wind GIA”) which provides for Interconnection Services (as defined in the Rush Springs Wind GIA) for a Generating Facility with an aggregate capacity not to exceed 250 MW; WHEREAS, Rush Springs Storage entered into a certain GIA by and among itself, SPP, and AEP, dated as of February 6, 2019 (the “Rush Springs Storage GIA” and, together with the Rush Springs Wind GIA, the “GIAs”) which provides for Interconnection Services (as defined in the Rush Springs Storage GIA) for 20 MW; WHEREAS, Rush Springs Wind owns certain personal property, fixtures, equipment and/or facilities (including the Interconnection Customer’s Interconnection Facilities, as identified in Appendix A to the Rush Springs Wind GIA) described in Exhibit A attached hereto (the “Shared Facilities”) that are necessary to interconnect the Projects to the electric transmission system of AEP; WHEREAS, Rush Springs Wind and Rush Springs Storage are entering into this Shared Facilities Agreement to allow Rush Springs Storage to use the Shared Facilities as necessary for it to be able to operate its Project and deliver energy to and withdraw energy from the transmission system of AEP; and NOW THEREFORE, in consideration of the premises and of the mutual covenants and agreements contained herein, and for other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which is hereby acknowledged, the Parties hereby agree as follows: AGREEMENT TERM; EARLY TERMINATION Term. The term of this Agreement shall commence on the Effective Date and shall continue in effect until terminated (a) by mutual agreement of the Parties, or (b) pursuant to Section 1.2 of this Agreement. Early Termination. This Agreement shall automatically terminate, without further action by any Party and without further liability of any Party to any other Party (except for obligations accruing prior to the termination), upon the date that Rush Springs Wind or Rush Springs Storage shall have permanently ceased operation of its respective Project. GRANT OF SHARED FACILITIES RIGHTS Grant. Rush Springs Wind hereby grants to Rush Springs Storage, during the term of this Agreement, and on the terms and subject to the conditions hereof, the non-exclusive right to access and utilize the Shared Facilities as may be reasonably necessary in connection with the Interconnection Service received by Rush Springs Storage from SPP and AEP, and ownership, operation and maintenance of the Rush Springs Storage Project. The grant of rights under this Agreement by Rush Springs Wind to Rush Springs Storage is made only to the extent that such rights do not limit in any material respect the ability of Rush Springs Wind to comply with the terms and conditions of the Rush Springs Wind GIA. Essential Nature. Rush Springs Wind hereby acknowledges that the right of Rush Springs Storage to access and utilize the Shared Facilities is essential to the injection of electric energy from the Rush Springs Storage Project to the transmission system of AEP and withdrawal of energy by the Rush Springs Storage Project from the transmission system. Vesting. The right to access and utilize the Shared Facilities granted hereunder by Rush Springs Wind to Rush Springs Storage shall vest in Rush Springs Storage as a contracting party hereunder without any transfer of title, leasehold or other interest or rights in the Shared Facilities. NATURE OF SHARED FACILITIES RIGHTS Nature of Services. The Parties acknowledge that the grant of rights under this Agreement by Rush Springs Wind to Rush Springs Storage is made for the purpose of enabling the energy from Rush Springs Storage to reach the transmission system of AEP, and for energy from the transmission system of AEP to reach Rush Springs Storage. For the avoidance of doubt, the grant of rights under this Agreement by Rush Springs Wind to Rush Springs Storage shall not (i) adversely affect the operations or profitability of the Rush Springs Wind Project in any respect or (ii) to the extent compatible with the foregoing clause (i), limit the ability of any Party to perform its obligations under any agreement, as the same may hereafter be modified or amended, that such Party has entered into or enters into after the date hereof. Obligations of Rush Springs Wind. Rush Springs Wind shall exercise its rights and perform its obligations under this Agreement in a manner consistent with its obligations under the Rush Springs Wind GIA. Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, during the term of this Agreement, Rush Springs Wind agrees to: perform its obligations under this Agreement and the Rush Springs Wind GIA in accordance with Good Utility Practice, Applicable Laws and Regulations and Applicable Reliability Standards, in each case as defined in the Rush Springs Wind GIA, and in a manner consistent with the terms of the Rush Springs Wind GIA; comply with all provisions of the Rush Springs Wind GIA (including, without limitation, all insurance requirements, payments due, operational limits, operating guides, operating procedures and reliability standards and requirements applicable by virtue thereof); promptly provide to Rush Springs Storage any material notices it receives under the Rush Springs Wind GIA from SPP or AEP; and perform necessary maintenance on the Shared Facilities. Obligations of Rush Springs Storage. Rush Springs Storage shall exercise its rights and perform its obligations under this Agreement in a manner that is reasonable and facilitates Rush Springs Wind’s performance under, and compliance with, the Rush Springs Wind GIA. Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, during the term of this Agreement, Rush Springs Storage agrees to: operate the Rush Springs Storage Project and perform its obligations under this Agreement and the Rush Springs Storage GIA in accordance with Good Utility Practice, Applicable Laws and Regulations and Applicable Reliability Standards, in each case as defined in the Rush Springs Storage GIA, and in a manner consistent with the terms of the Rush Springs Storage GIA; facilitate Rush Springs Wind’s compliance with all provisions of the Rush Springs Wind GIA (including, without limitation, all insurance requirements, operational limits, operating guides, operating procedures and reliability standards and requirements applicable by virtue thereof) as related to the Rush Springs Storage Project; not take any action (or refrain from taking any action) which would result in a breach of the Rush Springs Wind GIA by Rush Springs Wind; use all commercially reasonable efforts to promptly resolve any technical issues arising in connection with the operation of the Rush Springs Storage Project that might reasonably be expected to result in a default under the Rush Springs Wind GIA, and if such default occurs, to promptly assist Rush Springs Wind in curing such default in accordance with the terms of the Rush Springs Wind GIA; comply with all instructions, as may be communicated to it by Rush Springs Wind, in order to ensure compliance with the provisions of the Rush Springs Wind GIA; provide Rush Springs Wind with all reasonable information regarding the operation and condition of the Rush Springs Storage Project required for Rush Springs Wind to maintain compliance with the terms and conditions of the Rush Springs Wind GIA; promptly provide to Rush Springs Wind copies of all notices and instructions received by Rush Springs Storage that affect Rush Springs Wind’s performance under the Rush Springs Wind GIA; and provide payment to Rush Springs Wind within ten (10) Business Days following receipt of demand therefor for (a) lost revenues any time the Rush Springs Wind Project is curtailed, disconnected, or experiences an outage due to actions or inactions by Rush Springs Storage due to interconnection activities, operations and maintenance, or other reasons, with such lost revenues including all revenues that Rush Springs Wind would have earned for energy, green attributes, capacity, or other products it would have sold under the applicable agreements to which it is a party, (b) availability incentive or bonus payments lost, or (c) other penalties, costs or charges incurred by Rush Springs Wind, as a direct result of any interruptions or curtailments of output from the Rush Springs Wind Project; in each case, such payments made or to be made by Rush Springs Storage shall be reduced by any insurance proceeds actually received by Rush Springs Wind in connection with the events described in subclauses (a), (b) or (c) of this Section 3.3(viii). No Joint and Several Liability between Rush Springs Wind and Rush Springs Storage. The Parties acknowledge that this Agreement does not subject either Party to joint and several liability for any actions taken by the other Party. Assignment or Transfer of Rights. Except as set forth in Section 9.6 hereof, Rush Springs Wind and Rush Springs Storage, respectively, shall not assign or transfer any rights granted to such Party hereunder with regard to the Shared Facilities, or grant any permission, license, right of way or similar right with regard to the Shared Facilities, without the prior written consent of the other Party. Interference. Subject to the terms of this Agreement, in no event shall any Party be entitled to exercise its rights to access and utilize the Shared Facilities if the exercise of such rights would materially interfere with or limit the reasonable and necessary access and utilization of the Shared Facilities by any other Party. Prior Written Consent. Except as set forth in this Agreement, without the prior written consent of such other Party, neither Party shall take any action that results in (a) the forbearance, foreclosure, termination or alteration of the respective rights of the other party or (ii) increases the obligations or responsibilities of the other Party, in each case, with respect to such Party’s access to, utilization of or reliance upon the Shared Facilities. MAINTENANCE OF SHARED FACILITIES; SUCCESSOR AGREEMENT; METERING Allocation of Certain Costs and Expenses. Rush Springs Wind shall be responsible for the operation, inspection, maintenance, repair, alteration, relocation, improvement and replacement of the Shared Facilities; provided, however, that the Parties hereby agree that (a) the costs and expenses of the operation, inspection, maintenance, repair, alteration, relocation, improvement and replacement of the Shared Facilities and of insuring the Shared Facilities, and (b) costs that Rush Springs Wind is responsible for under the Rush Springs Wind GIA, including potential costs under Section 10.5 for operations and maintenance expenses ((a) and (b), collectively, “Costs”), and which are not directly caused by an identified Party under this Agreement, shall be shared between Rush Springs Wind and Rush Springs Storage on a pro rata basis based on the relative MW percentage of a Party’s respective Project to the total MWs of the Projects combined, with Rush Springs Wind, based on its current size of approximately 249.9 MW, paying 96.04% of the Costs and Rush Springs Storage, based on its anticipated size of approximately 10.3 MW, paying 3.96% of the Costs, such numbers to be adjusted between the parties if project sizes change. Each Party shall be responsible for all Costs that are directly caused by such Party or its respective Project. Rush Springs Storage shall pay its respective allocation (specified above) of such Costs to Rush Springs Wind within twenty (20) days of receipt from Rush Springs Wind of written notice specifying such Costs, provided that the payment obligations of Rush Springs Storage shall not commence until it starts injecting or withdrawing energy over the Shared Facilities. Rush Springs Wind and Rush Springs Storage shall each be liable to pay for the station power service of their respective Projects. Successor Agreement. In the event that the Shared Facilities are no longer operated and maintained only by Rush Springs Wind for any reason, the Parties agree to use good faith efforts to negotiate mutually agreeable terms and execute a mutually agreeable agreement (or amendment to this Agreement) that specifies the division of responsibilities of the entities providing operation and maintenance services associated with the Shared Facilities. Metering Protocol. The Parties agree to enter into a separate metering agreement to address allocation of the following items among the Projects in a manner that ensures Rush Springs Wind revenues are not adversely impacted as a result of the use of the Shared Facilities by Rush Springs Storage: (A) the energy output and usage of the applicable Projects, (B) associated losses, and (C) payments associated with the Projects’ energy output, usage, and losses. CHANGE IN LAW Change in Law. In the event that a change in the laws or regulations applicable to the Shared Facilities, any of the Projects, or this Agreement requires the amendment, modification or replacement of this Agreement in order to satisfy any applicable federal, state or local regulatory requirements, the Parties agree to use good faith efforts to negotiate and implement mutually agreeable terms to accomplish such amendment, modification or replacement. CERTAIN COVENANTS Authority and Operational Abilities. Each of the Parties represents, as of the Effective Date, and covenants for the term of this Agreement, that such Party has the legal authority and operational abilities to fulfill its obligations under this Agreement. Agreement to Cooperate. Each Party agrees to reasonably cooperate with the other Parties so that, subject to the terms of this Agreement, each Project benefits from the full utilization and enjoyment of the Shared Facilities as is necessary for the efficient operation of each such Project. Adverse Events. If an operational issue arises at the Rush Springs Wind Project or Rush Springs Storage Project that is reasonably expected to result in a material breach by Rush Springs Wind of the Rush Springs Wind GIA or this Agreement or if required to comply with any applicable SPP Tariff requirements (as defined in the Rush Springs Wind GIA and the Rush Springs Storage GIA) (an “Adverse Event”), Rush Springs Wind shall curtail the Project that is causing the Adverse Event. In the event of such curtailment, energy deliveries to or withdrawals from the Point of Interconnection from the Project that has caused the Adverse Event shall be limited as necessary until the Adverse Event has been cured in the reasonable judgment of Rush Springs Wind. If, as a direct result of an Adverse Event caused by either Project, Rush Springs Wind incurs costs, expenses, or penalties of any kind (“AE Costs”), the Party owning the Project that caused such Adverse Event shall be solely responsible for such AE Costs. In the event that both Projects are responsible for the Adverse Event, and to the extent that Rush Springs Wind, in its sole and absolute discretion, can accurately allocate responsibility for such Adverse Event between the Projects, Rush Springs Wind shall be responsible for only its allocable portion of such applicable AE Costs and Rush Springs Wind shall allocate the remaining AE Costs to Rush Springs Storage. If, however, it is not reasonably possible for Rush Springs Wind, as determined in its sole and absolute discretion, to accurately allocate such responsibility, Rush Springs Wind shall be liable for 96.04% of such AE Costs and Rush Springs Storage shall be liable for 3.96% of such AE Costs. MATERIAL BREACH; LIMITATIONS Material Breach by any Party. In the event of any material breach of this Agreement by any Party and such Party fails to promptly cure such breach within a reasonable time not to exceed thirty (30) days after receipt of written notice from the other, non-defaulting Party describing such breach, the non-defaulting Party shall have the right, but not the obligation, in addition to all remedies available to it at law or in equity, to (i) cure the breach on behalf of the defaulting Party, or (ii) if Rush Springs Wind is the non-breaching Party, suspend Rush Springs Storage’s access to all or any portion of the Shared Facilities for so long as such default shall be continuing and remain uncured. Notwithstanding the foregoing, in the event that a breach of this Agreement could give rise to a breach by Rush Springs Wind pursuant to the terms of the Rush Springs Wind GIA, the non-defaulting Party shall not be required to provide the defaulting Party with notice and/or an opportunity to cure in order to exercise the remedies specified in clause (i) or (ii) above; provided, that the remedy specified in clause (i) may be exercised, without prejudice to any right or remedy of any Party hereunder, by any lender or investor of such Party. If a Party (or any lender or investor thereof) chooses to cure a Party’s default, the defaulting Party shall reimburse the non-defaulting Party (or such Party’s lender or investor) upon demand for all commercially reasonable costs incurred by the non-defaulting Party (or such Party’s lender or investor) in curing such default. Except for indemnification obligations related to third-party claims as provided for in Section 9.7, in no event shall any Party be liable under any provision of this Agreement for any special, indirect, incidental, consequential, or punitive damages including, but not limited to, loss of profit or revenue, loss of the use of equipment, cost of capital, cost of temporary equipment or services, whether based in whole or in part in contract, in tort, including negligence, strict liability, or any other theory of liability. FORCE MAJEURE Force Majeure. In the event of an act of God, government order or restraint, war (declared or undeclared) or warlike conditions, act of terrorism, blockade, revolution, strike, lockout, civil commotion, fire, flood, storm, epidemic or any other occurrence beyond a Party’s reasonable control (each a “Force Majeure Event”), such Party shall promptly notify the other Party thereof and, so long as such condition shall persist, such Party shall not be liable for the delay in performance of, or the failure to perform, its obligations (other than obligations for payment of amounts due hereunder) under this Agreement caused directly or indirectly thereby. The claiming Party shall give each other Party notice describing the particulars of the Force Majeure Event. Within fifteen (15) days after giving notice of the Force Majeure Event, the claiming Party shall give each other Party an estimate of the Force Majeure Event’s expected duration and probable impact. The claiming Party shall continue to furnish each other Party with timely regular reports during the continuation of the Force Majeure Event. Each Party shall promptly exercise commercially reasonable efforts to mitigate or limit the impact to its obligations hereunder as a result of the Force Majeure Event. MISCELLANEOUS Relationship of Parties. The Parties do not intend to create hereby any joint venture, partnership, association or any other entity for the conduct of any business. Except as provided in Section 7.1, nothing herein shall be deemed to authorize any Party to act on behalf of any other Party. Non-Interference. Each Party agrees not to interfere with the reasonable and necessary utilization of the Shared Facilities by any other Party as permitted hereunder. Modification and Amendment. The terms of this Agreement may only be modified or amended in a writing signed by all Parties. Waiver. The failure of a Party to insist upon or enforce strict performance of any of the provisions of this Agreement or to exercise any rights or remedies under this Agreement shall not be construed as a waiver or relinquishment to any extent of such Party’s right to assert or rely upon any such provisions, rights, and remedies in that or any other instance; rather, the same shall be and remain in full force and effect. Enforceability. Any provision of this Agreement which is prohibited or unenforceable in any jurisdiction shall, as to such jurisdiction, be ineffective only to the extent of such prohibition, but shall be effective to the extent of such remaining provisions hereof. Assignment. No Party may assign any of its benefits, rights or obligations hereunder to any third party without the prior written consent of the other Party, provided, however, that either Party may collaterally assign this Agreement to any lender in connection with a financing or a refinancing of its respective Project. Indemnification. Each Party shall indemnify, defend and hold each other Party, its officers, directors, shareholders, members and affiliates, harmless from any and all damages, losses, claims, including claims and actions relating to injury to or death of any person or damage to property, demand, suits, recoveries, costs and expenses, court costs, attorney fees, and all other obligations by or to third parties, arising out of or resulting from the indemnifying Party’s performance or non-performance of its obligations under this Agreement, except in cases of gross negligence or intentional wrongdoing, by the indemnified Party. Choice of Law, Jurisdiction and Waiver of Jury Trial (i) This Agreement and the rights and obligations of the Parties hereunder will be governed pursuant to, and enforced, construed and interpreted in accordance with, the laws of the State of New York without regard to principles of conflicts of laws (other than Section 5-1401 of the General Obligations Law of the State of New York). Venue for resolution of any disputes under this Agreement shall be New York County, New York. (ii) Each of the Parties irrevocably and unconditionally submits to the exclusive jurisdiction of the United States District Court for the Southern District of New York for the purposes of any suit, action or other proceeding arising out of or relating to this Agreement, the transactions contemplated hereby, any provision hereof or the breach, performance, enforcement or validity or invalidity of this Agreement or any provision hereof (and agrees not to commence any suit, action or proceeding relating thereto except in such courts). (iii) THE PARTIES HERETO EACH HEREBY KNOWINGLY, VOLUNTARILY AND INTENTIONALLY WAIVE THE RIGHT EACH MAY HAVE TO A TRIAL BY JURY WITH RESPECT TO ANY PROCEEDINGS BASED HEREON, OR ARISING OUT OF, UNDER OR IN CONNECTION WITH THIS AGREEMENT, OR ANY COURSE OF CONDUCT, COURSE OF DEALING, STATEMENTS (WHETHER ORAL OR WRITTEN) OR ACTIONS OF EITHER PARTY TO THIS AGREEMENT. THIS PROVISION IS A MATERIAL INDUCEMENT FOR THE PARTIES TO ENTER INTO THIS AGREEMENT. Inspection of Records. Each Party shall have access to any records concerning the Shared Facilities held by any other Party upon reasonable notice and at reasonable times. Entire Agreement. This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement of the Parties with respect to the subject matter hereof. Section Headings. The section headings in this Agreement are for convenience of reference only and shall not modify, define, expand, or limit any of the terms or provisions hereof. Counterparts. This Agreement may be executed in one or more counterparts, each of which when so executed shall be deemed an original, and all of which when taken together shall constitute one and the same instrument. Specific Performance. The Parties hereto may demand specific performance of this Agreement. Each Party hereby irrevocably waives any defense based on the adequacy of a remedy at law and any other defense which might be asserted to bar the remedy of specific performance. Obligation to Notify in Case of Termination. The Parties shall notify AEP and SPP within 10 business days if the Agreement is terminated. If the Agreement is terminated, other than as a result of the Parties being owned by the same entity(ies), the Parties shall be deemed in breach of their respective GIAs in accordance with Article 17 of each GIA, unless such breach can be cured by the Generator Parties agreeing to reinstate the Agreement or to enter into a similar agreement acceptable materially comparable to this Agreement or by the Parties entering some other comparable arrangement that enables the Parties to deliver energy from their respective Projects to the Point of Interconnection and to comply with all other terms and conditions set forth in their respective GIAs. Development of Rush Springs Expansion Project. If Rush Springs Wind Expansion, LLC (“Rush Springs Expansion”) develops its 250 MW wind energy project in the same vicinity as the Parties’ projects and requires use of the Shared Facilities to deliver its energy to the point of interconnection with AEP, the Parties shall reasonably cooperate with Rush Springs Expansion to amend this Agreement to add Rush Springs Expansion. Insurance. Rush Springs Storage shall maintain insurance at substantially the same levels and with insurers rated as set forth in Schedule 9.16 attached.
IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the Parties have caused this Shared Facilities Agreement to be executed as of the date first written above.
